Also, I will return 400 Bad Request for incorrect body schema.\n\n\n**Defining Project PATCH Logic**\n\nI am now defining the PATCH method for updating existing projects. The focus is to include authentication, role checks, and project retrieval based on the ID extracted from the route. Client roles will need project-specific access verification, returning a 403 error for unauthorized access. For admins, the implementation will support updating project data, including detailed error handling and type checking.\n\n\n\n**Defining Project PATCH/DELETE**\n\nI'm now outlining the `PATCH` and `DELETE` methods for project updates and removal. I'm focusing on strict authentication and authorization checks, with `401` Unauthorized for invalid access. Non-admin roles will receive `403 Forbidden` for both. For `PATCH`, I will validate input, allow admin updates, and handle changes to the `client_id` field. I will return `404 Not Found` if the project isn't found and `400 Bad Request` for data errors.\n\n\n"}}
