{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:06:33.428Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Constructing API Routes**\n\nI'm now setting up the API routes, specifically the directories for projects under `/app/api/v1/`. I plan to write `route.ts` files for both the base `/projects` and the dynamic `/projects/[id]` endpoints. Before I dive in, I'm checking the existing user route to understand the import conventions for the `lib/api-auth` library.\n\n\n**Verifying Directory Depth**\n\nI've confirmed the relative path from the project route to the authentication library. It's indeed four levels up, as initially calculated. However, I've decided to switch to using an absolute path alias, specifically `@/lib/api-auth`, because this is both cleaner and safer, according to the Next.js conventions and the observed usage in the `/app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts` file. While relative paths work, absolute paths are less error-prone.\n\n\n**Confirming Authentication Path**\n\nI'm now sticking with a relative path for the authentication import, specifically `../../../../lib/api-auth`, to avoid `tsc` compilation issues in testing scripts. This feels like the right approach, after observing the existing code base. Now I'll proceed to design and then write the code for `app/api/v1/projects/route.ts`. The design will be the following: GET will list projects with filters (client\\_id, phase, status, health, owner, and search). It will be restricted to the client's own `client_id` if they are a client role. POST will create a project and is restricted to the admin role. I plan to copy the `getAuthCaller` function from `users/route.ts` for this endpoint.\n\n\n**Implementing GET Logic**\n\nNow I'm focusing on implementing the GET method. I have integrated the `getAuthCaller` function into the GET method and handling cases where authentication fails. I have implemented a conditional, checking for an authentication `status` in the return object from the function. The next step is to prepare a successful GET response, and determine how to incorporate filter options.\n\n\n**Refining Filter Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the filter logic within the GET method. I've successfully extracted query parameters like `client_id`, `phase`, and others from the URL. I'm handling client role restrictions; clients can only see their projects. I am filtering the project list based on the user's `client_id`, when the user is not an admin, and blocking clients from querying other client IDs.\n\n\n**Finalizing Filter Application**\n\nI am now completing the filter application for the GET method. I've integrated filtering based on `phase`, `status`, `health`, `owner`, and a general `search` query across project names and descriptions. The logic accurately filters the projects array based on these parameters. I'm satisfied that these filters handle all the cases.\n\n\n**Adding POST Endpoint Logic**\n\nI am now focusing on the POST method implementation. I have successfully integrated authentication, ensuring only admins can create new projects. I'm extracting and handling the request body, including error handling for invalid JSON. The next step will be to create the new project.\n\n\n**Validating Input Parameters**\n\nI'm now implementing input validation for the POST method. I've added checks for all required fields like `name` and `client_id`, returning a 400 error with descriptive messages if these are missing or invalid. I have added a `client_id` whitelist and return a 400 error if the value is invalid. I will now create the project with these parameters.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:06:33.430Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"8kat7bx2","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/projects/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_PROJECTS, \n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  ApiProject, \n  getNextProjectId, \n  getClientNameFromId, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const { searchParams } = new URL(req.url);\n    const clientIdFilter = searchParams.get(\"client_id\");\n    const phaseFilter = searchParams.get(\"phase\");\n    const statusFilter = searchParams.get(\"status\");\n    const healthFilter = searchParams.get(\"health\");\n    const ownerFilter = searchParams.get(\"owner\");\n    const searchQuery = searchParams.get(\"search\");\n\n    let projects = Object.values(API_MOCK_PROJECTS) as ApiProject[];\n\n    // RBAC policy logic\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      projects = projects.filter(p => p.client_id === callerClientId);\n\n      // Enforce client boundaries\n      if (clientIdFilter && clientIdFilter !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied to requested client's projects.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    } else {\n      // Admin filter\n      if (clientIdFilter) {\n        projects = projects.filter(p => p.client_id === clientIdFilter);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Apply specific filters\n    if (phaseFilter) {\n      const q = phaseFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      projects = projects.filter(p => p.phase.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (statusFilter) {\n      const q = statusFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      projects = projects.filter(p => p.status.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (healthFilter) {\n      const q = healthFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      projects = projects.filter(p => p.health.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (ownerFilter) {\n      const q = ownerFilter.toLowerCase().trim();\n      projects = projects.filter(p => p.owner.toLowerCase().includes(q));\n    }\n    if (searchQuery) {\n      const q = searchQuery.toLowerCase().trim();\n      projects = projects.filter(p => \n        p.name.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        p.desc.toLowerCase().includes(q) || \n        p.owner.toLowerCase().includes(q) ||\n        p.id.toLowerCase().includes(q)\n      );\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, projects });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    // MVP constraints: admin create/update/archive only\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators can create projects.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const { name, client_id, phase, status, health, owner, nodesCount, enclaveType, desc } = body;\n\n    if (!name || typeof name !== \"string\" || !name.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'name' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    if (!client_id || typeof client_id !== \"string\" || !client_id.trim()) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing or invalid 'client_id' field.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const validClients = [\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\"];\n    if (!validClients.includes(client_id)) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid 'client_id' specified.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const newProjId = getNextProjectId();\n    const newProj: ApiProject = {\n      id: newProjId,\n      name: name.trim(),\n      client_id: client_id,\n      client_name: getClientNameFromId(client_id),\n      phase: phase || \"Phase I: Planning\",\n      status: status || \"active\",\n      health: health || \"On Track\",\n      owner: owner || caller.name,\n      nodesCount: typeof nodesCount === \"number\" ? nodesCount : 1,\n      enclaveType: enclaveType || \"Intel SGX\",\n      desc: desc || \"\",\n      lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString()\n    };\n\n    (API_MOCK_PROJECTS as Record<string, ApiProject>)[newProjId] = newProj;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, project: newProj }, { status: 201 });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
