{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:06:53.566Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Crafting the Single Project Endpoint**\n\nI'm currently focused on designing the dynamic single-project endpoint, specifically `app/api/v1/projects/[id]/route.ts`. The design will need to accommodate GET and PATCH requests. GET will require authorization restrictions based on user role (admin) or client association. The PATCH method will handle updates.\n\n\n**Defining DELETE Operation**\n\nI've added the DELETE operation to the endpoint. It will allow project deletion, but for the MVP, access will be restricted to admins only. I've also outlined the structure of the `app/api/v1/projects/[id]/route.ts` file, and I'm ready to continue building it out.\n\n\n**Implementing GET Method Logic**\n\nI've completed the GET method logic within the endpoint. This includes implementing authorization checks based on the user's role and client association, which covers both admin and client-specific access restrictions, ensuring only authorized users can retrieve project details. I've also integrated error handling for cases like unauthorized access, project not found, and internal server errors.\n\n\n**Refining PATCH Method Logic**\n\nI'm currently refining the PATCH method within the endpoint to handle project updates. This includes comprehensive checks for the JSON body's validity, data type verification, and handling specific update scenarios such as name, client_id, phase, status, health, owner, nodesCount, enclaveType, and desc. I have added error responses for bad requests and input validation errors. I've also implemented authorization restrictions to ensure only admins can update projects as per the MVP constraints.\n\n\n**Validating Input Parameters**\n\nI'm now implementing thorough input validation within the PATCH method. I'm focusing on ensuring data integrity when updating project details. Specifically, I'm checking the project name format, the validity of the client ID against an array of valid clients. I'm also implementing type checking and error responses for updates to `phase`, `status`, and `health`, ensuring all updated parameters adhere to predefined formats.\n\n\n**Finalizing Update Validation**\n\nI'm now putting the finishing touches on the input validation within the PATCH method. I've covered owner, nodesCount, enclaveType, and desc, including the necessary type checks and specific error responses. This ensures all project updates are thoroughly vetted for data integrity before being saved, which completes the endpoint.\n\n\n**Implementing DELETE Operation**\n\nI've added the DELETE operation to the `app/api/v1/projects/[id]/route.ts` file. Authorization is in place, and only admins can delete projects per MVP constraints. I've also implemented error handling for unauthorized requests and project not found scenarios, ensuring a robust API response.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:06:53.568Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"jfzamvm3","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/projects/[id]/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  API_MOCK_PROJECTS, \n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  ApiProject, \n  getClientNameFromId, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation \n} from \"../../../../../lib/api-auth\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) return null;\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) return null;\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim()];\n  return user && user.status !== \"inactive\" ? user : null;\n}\n\nexport async function GET(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\", message: \"Invalid or expired credentials.\" },\n        { status: 401 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const project = (API_MOCK_PROJECTS as Record<string, ApiProject>)[id];\n    if (!project) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Not Found\", message: \"Project not found.\" },\n        { status: 404 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    // RBAC check: Client roles can only view their own projects\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      if (project.client_id !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json(\n          { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Access denied. Project belongs to another client.\" },\n          { status: 403 }\n        );\n      }\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, project });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function PATCH(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\", message: \"Invalid or expired credentials.\" },\n        { status: 401 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    // MVP restricts project updates to gff_admin\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators can update projects.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const { id } = await params;\n    const project = (API_MOCK_PROJECTS as Record<string, ApiProject>)[id];\n    if (!project) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Not Found\", message: \"Project not found.\" },\n        { status: 404 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const body = await req.json().catch(() => null);\n    if (!body) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid JSON body.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const { name, client_id, phase, status, health, owner, nodesCount, enclaveType, desc } = body;\n\n    if (name !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof name !== \"string\" || !name.trim()) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid project name.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      }\n      project.name = name.trim();\n    }\n\n    if (client_id !== undefined) {\n      const validClients = [\"client-001\", \"client-002\", \"client-003\", \"client-004\"];\n      if (!validClients.includes(client_id)) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid client_id specified.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      }\n      project.client_id = client_id;\n      project.client_name = getClientNameFromId(client_id);\n    }\n\n    if (phase !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof phase !== \"string\") return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid phase.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      project.phase = phase;\n    }\n\n    if (status !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof status !== \"string\") return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid status.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      project.status = status;\n    }\n\n    if (health !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof health !== \"string\") return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid health.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      project.health = health;\n    }\n\n    if (owner !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof owner !== \"string\") return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid owner.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      project.owner = owner;\n    }\n\n    if (nodesCount !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof nodesCount !== \"number\") return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"nodesCount must be a number.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      project.nodesCount = nodesCount;\n    }\n\n    if (enclaveType !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof enclaveType !== \"string\") return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid enclaveType.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      project.enclaveType = enclaveType;\n    }\n\n    if (desc !== undefined) {\n      if (typeof desc !== \"string\") return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid desc.\" }, { status: 400 });\n      project.desc = desc;\n    }\n\n    project.lastUpdated = new Date().toISOString();\n\n    (API_MOCK_PROJECTS as Record<string, ApiProject>)[id] = project;\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, project });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function DELETE(req: Request, { params }: { params: any }) {\n  try {\n    const caller = getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (!caller) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Unauthorized\", message: \"Invalid or expired credentials.\" },\n        { status: 401 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    // MVP restricts deletes to gff_admin\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Only administrators can delete projects.\" },\n        { status: 403 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    const { id } = await params;\n    if (!(API_MOCK_PROJECTS as Record<string, ApiProject>)[id]) {\n      return NextResponse.json(\n        { success: false, error: \"Not Found\", message: \"Project not found.\" },\n        { status: 404 }\n      );\n    }\n\n    delete (API_MOCK_PROJECTS as Record<string, ApiProject>)[id];\n\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: true, message: \"Project successfully deleted.\" });\n  } catch (err) {\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}\n"}}}
