{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:09:07.155Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"akosra4r","input":{"summary":"I have successfully implemented the MVP Projects CRUD APIs under `/api/v1/projects` as specified. Here is a summary of the implementation:\n\n### 1. Files Changed & Created:\n- **`lib/api-auth.ts`** (Modified): \n  - Defined the `ApiProject` interface with high-fidelity fields: `id`, `name`, `client_id`, `client_name`, `phase`, `status`, `health`, `owner`, `nodesCount`, `enclaveType`, `desc`, `lastUpdated`.\n  - Added an in-memory database store `API_MOCK_PROJECTS` initialized globally to ensure persistence across API requests.\n  - Added robust helper functions: `getNextProjectId()`, `getClientNameFromId()`, and `getClientIdFromAssociation()`.\n- **`app/api/v1/projects/route.ts`** (Created):\n  - Created the general endpoint handling `GET` (listing) and `POST` (creation).\n  - Implemented advanced filters: `client_id` (admin-only), `phase`, `status`, `health`, `owner`, and `search` (multi-field keyword match).\n  - Enforced strict RBAC: Admin roles can access everything, while client roles are restricted to viewing only projects matching their associated client ID.\n- **`app/api/v1/projects/[id]/route.ts`** (Created):\n  - Created the dynamic endpoint handling `GET` (retrieve single project), `PATCH` (update), and `DELETE` (delete).\n  - Handled input validation for partial updates (`PATCH`), returning `400 Bad Request` on invalid inputs.\n  - Blocked non-authorized tenants (clients querying projects of other clients) with `403 Forbidden` responses.\n- **`scripts/test-project-apis.js`** (Created):\n  - Built an automated integration test script that compiles and executes exhaustive test scenarios verifying authentications, filters, individual lookups, cross-tenant protection, and CRUD operations.\n\n### 2. Validation Performed:\n- Executed `scripts/test-project-apis.js` locally. The verification suite successfully passed all tests:\n  - Auth/status checks (active/inactive user gates and Bearer tokens checks) are fully functional.\n  - Multi-tenant list scoping filters projects exactly by `client_id` (e.g., Sarah Jenkins only gets `client-004`).\n  - Search keyword queries find appropriate target fields.\n  - Individual retrieval validates both successful lookups and cross-tenant `403 Forbidden` boundaries.\n  - Project creation is blocked for client roles but successfully provisions and maps client names for admin users.\n  - Project modifications (`PATCH`) and deletions (`DELETE`) correctly update/remove states inside global database memory.\n- Executed existing verification suites (`test-user-apis.js` and `verify-auth-endpoints.js`) to guarantee zero regressions. All tests are perfectly green!\n\n### 3. Limitations:\n- Standard Next.js server-side memory persistence is utilized for mock DB storage as database engines are excluded per project guidelines. Data persists seamlessly across API requests and reloads.","verified":true}}}
